body:
Consider the test case below.  A temporary is made for 610, which is output after the first if block.  Verilog requires variable declarations to be at the beginning of blocks.

```mlir
module {
  rtl.module @foobar(%clock: i1, %arg1: i1, %arg2: i1, %arg3: i1) {
    sv.always posedge %clock  {
        sv.if %arg1  {
          sv.fatal
        }
        //this forces a common subexpression to be output out-of-line
        %610 = comb.and %arg1, %arg2 : i1
        %611 = comb.and %arg3, %610 : i1
        sv.if %610  {
          sv.fatal
        }
        sv.if %611  {
          sv.fatal
        }
    }
    rtl.output
  }
}
```
